
.TH "GCLOUD_COMPUTE_INSTANCE\-GROUPS_MANAGED_RECREATE\-INSTANCES" 1



.SH "NAME"
.HP
gcloud compute instance\-groups managed recreate\-instances \- recreate instances managed by a managed instance group



.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP
\f5gcloud compute instance\-groups managed recreate\-instances\fR \fINAME\fR \fB\-\-instances\fR \fIINSTANCE\fR,[\fIINSTANCE\fR,...] [\fB\-\-zone\fR\ \fIZONE\fR] [\fIGLOBAL\-FLAG\ ...\fR]



.SH "DESCRIPTION"

\fBgcloud compute instance\-groups managed recreate\-instances\fR is used to
recreate one or more instances in a managed instance group. The underlying
virtual machine instances are deleted and recreated based on the latest instance
template configured for the managed instance group.



.SH "POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS"

\fINAME\fR
.RS 2m
Managed instance group name.


.RE

.SH "REQUIRED FLAGS"

\fB\-\-instances\fR \fIINSTANCE\fR,[\fIINSTANCE\fR,...]
.RS 2m
Names of instances to recreate.


.RE

.SH "OPTIONAL FLAGS"

\fB\-\-zone\fR \fIZONE\fR
.RS 2m
The zone of the instance group manager to recreate instances. If not specified,
you will be prompted to select a zone.

To avoid prompting when this flag is omitted, you can set the
\f5\fIcompute/zone\fR\fR property:

.RS 2m
$ gcloud config set compute/zone ZONE
.RE

A list of zones can be fetched by running:

.RS 2m
$ gcloud compute zones list
.RE

To unset the property, run:

.RS 2m
$ gcloud config unset compute/zone
.RE

Alternatively, the zone can be stored in the environment variable
\f5\fICLOUDSDK_COMPUTE_ZONE\fR\fR.


.RE

.SH "GLOBAL FLAGS"

Run \fB$ gcloud help\fR for a description of flags available to all commands.
